## Description {#details}

This header provides internal APIs and implementation details used by the pass management interfaces exposed in PassManager.h.

To understand more context of why these particular interfaces are needed, see that header file. None of these APIs should be used elsewhere.

<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Method to try and mark a result as invalid.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="130"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="131"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// When the outer analysis manager detects a change in some underlying</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// unit of the IR, it will call this method on all of the results cached.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p PA is a set of preserved analyses which can be used to avoid</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// invalidation because the pass which changed the underlying IR took care</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// to update or preserve the analysis result in some way.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p Inv is typically a \\c AnalysisManager::Invalidator object that can be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// used by a particular analysis result to discover if other analyses</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="140"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// results are also invalidated in the event that this result depends on</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="142"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="143"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\returns true if the result is indeed invalid (the default).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
